The paper focuses on cross-modal retrieval between textual and visual data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves deep learning architectures, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on multimedia datasets (cs.MM) and proposes a stochastic batch-wise training routine, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms (cs.LG).
